###FALLING IN LOVE ... in LA LA LAND Apr 29 ~  May 10

Find connection, find love; ride the rollercoaster of pleasure, pain, agony & ecstasy.

'Every person is a world to explore....You are part of the universe, you are made of stars. When you look at your loved one, you see they are also made of stars... in this way we naturally feel reverence.

Understanding someone’s suffering is the best gift you can give another person.
 
Understanding is love’s other name. 
If you don’t understand, you can’t love.'
Thích Nhất Hạnh


###FALLING IN LOVE is curated by CryptoChild

###From TrasHarts 1.0 

(the first NFT with 50% royalty):

Give your heart away. Completely.
Be prepared for it be bruised, torn out and shredded.
Without this commitment, the joy and happiness of love cannot truly be experienced.

“If a person has never suffered, he or she will never be able to know happiness”

“No mud, no lotus”

Thich Nhat Hahn

Cont... TrasHarts 2.0

“No mud, no lotus”
Thich Nhat Hahn

The heart is still bruised and regularly shredded.
The desire to love, to be loved, remains.
Love blurs the lines between giving and receiving but as they are now lines drawn, does that mean that love is lost?

Or if challenged by Krishnamurti, was it ever love at all?
  
"Why is there this everlasting craving to be loved? ... You want to be loved because you do not love; but the moment you love, it is finished... Without love you are a dead thing; and when the dead thing asks for love, it is still dead. Whereas, if your heart is full of love, then you never ask to be loved, you never put out your begging bowl for someone to fill it. It is only the empty who ask to be filled, and an empty heart can never be filled by ... seeking love in a hundred other ways.”

For those that want to know true love and how to love deeply  - “TRUE LOVE: A Practice for Awakening the Heart” by Thich Nhât Hành:

To love deeply you put yourself in a position to be hurt - deeply.
There is no other way.
